{block content}
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <h1 n:block="title">How to reach to ...</h1>
        <h2>hotel PLUS Prague ?</h2>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">web hotel:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.plushostels.com/en/plusprague" target="_blank">http://www.plushostels.com/en/plusprague</a></li>
            <li class="list-group-item">city transport:&nbsp;<a href="http://spojeni.dpp.cz/" target="_blank">http://spojeni.dpp.cz/</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="vgap-1"></div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
        <p>
            The best way how to get from the airport, the bus station or the train station is by the public transport (subway, bus or tram). It is the fastest and the cheapest way. First, how to buy a transport ticket? It is easy, you can buy them almost everywhere at metro stations and surface transport stops in the orange ticket machines. You can set up a language into english and few other languages. Payment is with coins or credit cards. There are different types according to the lenght of travel. The best one is for 30 or 90 minutes. They cost 24 and 32 CZK. Don't buy them for longer time, we have the tickets for you, for whole time of stay. They are included in the welcome package. The ticket apply for every type of transport. Don't forget to validate them! You can validate the tickets before you enter the subway through the orange machines or in the tram or bus.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-12">
